cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DS 

The paper focuses on the analysis of heterogeneous social networks and proposes a classifier based on the theory of belief functions to classify social messages based on their spreading in the network. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with the analysis of social networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). The proposed classifier uses AI techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the collection and processing of data, which falls under the sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
